description.narrative: COVID-19 and the change of a number of staff has impacted operations and our ability to achieve some of the planned activities both within UNICEF and with external partners. Nonetheless, progress is being made towards preparing for, and responding to disasters and advance UNICEF's climate change-related activities. Additionally, staff have worked diligently as part of the COVID-19 response leading the taskforce, development of the response plan, funding activities, leading an interagency RCCE group, and working to create COVID RCCE materials for vulnerable populations in IDP camps and non-governmental-controlled areas. Progress is also being made towards and interagency AAP platform. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:23/07/2020
